This paper is likely to belong to the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) as it introduces a new formulation of the axiom of dependent choice, which is a fundamental concept in mathematical logic. It may also belong to Programming Languages (cs.PL) as it discusses termination of rewrite systems, which is a key concept in programming language theory. Additionally, it may be relevant to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) as it considers termination principles for algorithms. It could also be relevant to Logic and Verification (cs.LM) as it discusses termination of formal systems. Finally, it may be relevant to Computational Complexity (cs.CC) as it relates to general termination theorems.
